The paper focuses on open relation extraction using deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of supervised training and neural architecture, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed model uses attention and convolution mechanisms, which are commonly used in neural networks for NLP tasks, such as sentiment analysis and text classification, suggesting cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval (IR) by extracting relation tuples from unstructured text, making cs.IR a plausible sub-category as well.
